# Protocol 27: Agent Execution Obligation (AGENT-EXEC-OBL)

> **Scope:** Agents run verifiable commands and processes themselves — they do not outsource runnable work to the human terminal.
> **Normative spec:** `gtcx-docs/docs/governance/protocols/27-agent-execution-obligation/protocol.md`
> **Phase:** 5.7 (follows 5.6 Proceed Brief)

## Rule

**You run commands; the human does not substitute for your shell.**

1. Before claiming done: run every applicable gate in the repo (`validate`, `lint`, `test`, `build`, story-specific smoke).
2. Report **command + exit code** — not "please run locally."
3. If blocked by permissions: emit **Permission Unblock Report** (enablement steps) — then re-run when unblocked.
4. Cross-repo code: execute in **owner repo** workspace, not gtcx-docs only.

## Verification ladder (V1–V6)

| Step | Command | Required |
| ---- | ------- | -------- |
| V1 | `git status`, `git diff` | Always |
| V2 | `pnpm format:check`, `pnpm lint`, `pnpm typecheck`, `pnpm architecture:check` | Documented gates |
| V3 | `pnpm test` | Tests exist for changed behavior |
| V4 | `pnpm docs:check-links`, `pnpm docs:check-frontmatter`, `pnpm bundle:check-budgets` | Docs/deploy/cross-repo probes |
| V5 | `pnpm quality:governance:check` | Governance changes |
| V6 | `cargo test`, `cargo test --features trusted-setup-verify --release` | Rust changes |

## Forbidden closing patterns

- "Verify locally: `cd gtcx-core && pnpm test`"
- "You should run the validators before merge"
- "Run this in your terminal and share the output"
- "Let me know when you've run the smoke test"

## Allowed patterns

- "Ran `pnpm run validate` — exit 0."
- "`pnpm test` failed: … — fixing …"
- "Blocked: `kubectl` denied by sandbox — **Permission Unblock Report** below; after you enable cluster access I will re-run apply."

## Permission Unblock Report template

```markdown
## Permission Unblock Report

**Blocked command:** `<exact command>`
**Exit / error:** `<stderr or tool message — no secrets>`
**Why blocked:** `<sandbox | network | aws | k8s | gh | file write | other>`
**Impact:** `<what cannot be verified or shipped until unblocked>`

### Enable (operator — one-time)

1. `<concrete step>`
2. `<optional second step>`

### After enable

Agent will re-run `<command>` in this session. Do not ask operator to paste terminal output unless debugging together.
```
